    b"\x00\x00\x0d\x0a        {{ _.role(\"system\") }}\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        You evaluate the conversation and "
    b"produce memory search hints for\x0a        the selected task.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        The hints "
    b"will drive memory search before the selected task runs.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        Stop once the"
    b" hints look good enough for the request without thinking about it too much.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a "
    b"       Search surfaces:\x0d\x0a        - tags: exact memory tags. They are not substri"
    b"ng searched.\x0d\x0a        - strings.contains: case-insensitive text fragments. Each "
    b"value is checked\x0d\x0a          as a substring against searchable memory content.\x0d\x0a "
    b"       - strings.equals: exact text values. Each value is checked for exact\x0d\x0a   "
    b"       equality against searchable memory content.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        Optional outputs a"
    b"vailable in this step:\x0d\x0a        - candidate_memory: a vague remembered observati"
    b"on that could be useful to\x0d\x0a          preserve.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        Rules:\x0d\x0a        - Ret"
    b"urn only search hints and optional candidate_memory.\x0d\x0a        - Search hints are"
    b" alternatives during retrieval; a memory can be useful\x0d\x0a          when any posit"
    b"ive tag or string hint matches.\x0d\x0a        - Prefer tags.any_of for positive tag h"
    b"ints.\x0d\x0a        - Leave tags.all_of empty unless compatibility with older memorie"
    b"s needs it.\x0d\x0a        - Use tags.none_of only for clear exclusions.\x0d\x0a        - Us"
    b"e strings.contains for durable words or phrases that should appear\x0d\x0a          in"
